<section class="container">
  <div class="section-header reveal">
    <div class="crosshair"></div>
    <span class="section-label">The Problem</span>
    <span class="section-index">01 / 09</span>
  </div>

  <div class="arch-list reveal">

    <div class="arch-item">
      <div class="arch-icon">
        <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-title-col">
        <h3 class="arch-title">Platforms Remember You. For Themselves.</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-desc-col">
        <p class="arch-desc">ChatGPT, Claude.ai, Gemini all have memory now. Try exporting it. Best you get: raw transcripts. Your context is their moat.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arch-item">
      <div class="arch-icon">
        <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M20 16V7a2 2 0 0 0-2-2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v9m16 0H4m16 0 1.28 2.55a1 1 0 0 1-.9 1.45H3.62a1 1 0 0 1-.9-1.45L4 16"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-title-col">
        <h3 class="arch-title">Memory-as-a-Service Is Still Lock-in.</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-desc-col">
        <p class="arch-desc">mem0 and supermemory add memory to your app. But data lives on their servers. They go down or raise prices -- your users lose everything.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arch-item">
      <div class="arch-icon">
        <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-title-col">
        <h3 class="arch-title">Remembering Everything Isn't Memory. It's Hoarding.</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-desc-col">
        <p class="arch-desc">RAG dumps everything into a vector store and hopes retrieval sorts it out. Real memory is knowing <em>what</em> matters, <em>when</em> to surface it, and <em>what to forget</em>. Filtering who, for what, and when -- that's the actual hard problem.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arch-item">
      <div class="arch-icon">
        <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M18 6 6 18"/><path d="m6 6 12 12"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-title-col">
        <h3 class="arch-title">Switch Tools. Keep Everything.</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-desc-col">
        <p class="arch-desc">Moved from Cursor to Claude Code? Your agent comes with you. New laptop? One import. Because with Signet, the knowledge was always yours.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
